                    <a href="/services" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary">View Services</a>
                </p>
        
                <p>
                    The services above use a variation of data models to exchange information and define taxonomies of data that can be reused across Cities
                    to improve interoperability and reuse of services.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <a href="/models" class="btn btn-lg btn-info">View Models</a>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
            <div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert" style="text-align:left">
              <p>
                  The term <b>AppStreams</b> comes from a combination of the ideas of Applications or APIs for Cities
                  and the Streams of Data those applications serve.
              </p>
                <p>
                    We are early in the journey but hope to create a set of easy to use Service and Data definitions for
                    Cities around the World.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If you have services or data related to Cities and want to suggest ideas or participate in the project, please
                    <a href="/contact">get in touch</a>.
                </p>
